<li id="cite_note-75"><span class="mw-cite-backlink noprint"><a href="#cite_ref-75">↑</a> </span><span class="reference-text"><span class="ouvrage" id="Taheri-Iraqi"><span class="ouvrage" id="Ahmad_Taheri-Iraqi">Ahmad <span class="nom_auteur">Taheri-Iraqi</span>, <cite class="italique">Zandaqa In The Early Abbasid Period With Special Reference To Poetry</cite>, University of Edinburgh, 3&#160;<abbr class="abbr" title="pages">p.</abbr><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Zandaqa+In+The+Early+Abbasid+Period+With+Special+Reference+To+Poetry&amp;rft.place=University+of+Edinburgh&amp;rft.aulast=Taheri-Iraqi&amp;rft.aufirst=Ahmad&amp;rft.tpages=3&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Ffr.wikipedia.org%3AHérésie"></span></span></span><blockquote>
<p>«&#160;Allthough the word zindīq/zandik was initially, in the Sassanid Empire, applied to Manichaeans as a pejorative epithet, by the time of the Islamic Epoch its usage had broadened and was loosely applied to Gnostic Dualists, Agnostics, Atheists and even free-thinkers and libertines. Eventually in the later period, even up to the present time, 'zindīq' came to be synonomous with 'irreligious'.&#160;»
</p>
</blockquote></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-a2-76"><span class="mw-cite-backlink noprint"><a href="#cite_ref-a2_76-0">↑</a> </span><span class="reference-text"><span class="ouvrage" id="Zaman,_Muhammad_Qasim.1997"><abbr class="abbr indicateur-langue" title="Langue : anglais">(en)</abbr> <span class="nom_auteur">Zaman, Muhammad Qasim.</span>, <cite class="italique" lang="en">Religion and politics under the early ʻAbbāsids&#160;: the emrgence of the proto-Sunnī elite</cite>, Leiden, Brill, <time>1997</time>, 232&#160;<abbr class="abbr" title="pages">p.</abbr> <small style="line-height:1em;">(<a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Spécial:Ouvrages_de_référence/90-04-10678-2" title="Spécial:Ouvrages de référence/90-04-10678-2"><span class="nowrap">90-04-10678-2</span></a> et <a href="/wiki/Spécial:Ouvrages_de_référence/978-90-04-10678-9" title="Spécial:Ouvrages de référence/978-90-04-10678-9"><span class="nowrap">978-90-04-10678-9</span></a>, <a href="/wiki/Online_Computer_Library_Center" title="Online Computer Library Center">OCLC</a>&#160;<span class="plainlinks noarchive nowrap"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://worldcat.org/fr/title/1038141926">1038141926</a></span>, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://worldcat.org/oclc/1038141926">lire en ligne</a>)</small><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Religion+and+politics+under+the+early+%CA%BBAbb%C4%81sids&amp;rft.place=Leiden&amp;rft.pub=Brill&amp;rft.stitle=the+emrgence+of+the+proto-Sunn%C4%AB+elite&amp;rft.aulast=Zaman%2C+Muhammad+Qasim.&amp;rft.date=1997&amp;rft.tpages=232&amp;rft.isbn=90-04-10678-2&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F1038141926&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Ffr.wikipedia.org%3AHérésie"></span></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-77"><span class="mw-cite-backlink noprint"><a href="#cite_ref-77">↑</a> </span><span class="reference-text">Fermée au <abbr class="abbr" title="9ᵉ siècle"><span class="romain">IX</span><sup style="font-size:72%">e</sup></abbr>&#160;siècle dans le <a href="/wiki/Sunnisme" title="Sunnisme">sunnisme</a>, rouverte au <abbr class="abbr" title="17ᵉ siècle"><span class="romain">XVII</span><sup style="font-size:72%">e</sup></abbr>&#160;siècle dans le <a href="/wiki/Chiisme" title="Chiisme">chiisme</a>.</span>
